In this article, President Donald Trump and his son-in-law, Jared Kushner, address a group of Jewish leaders and discuss their support for the Jewish people and the state of Israel. Trump highlights his decision to recognize Jerusalem as the capital of Israel and move the US embassy there. He also discusses his administration's efforts to reach a peace agreement between Israelis and Palestinians. Additionally, Trump mentions his decision to withdraw from the Iran nuclear deal and the impact it has had on Iran. Jewish leaders express their gratitude for Trump's support and ask about future plans regarding Iran. Overall, the article portrays Trump as a strong advocate for the Jewish people and the US-Israel relationship.